      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".] The right hand ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "gives",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", let not the left hand know it. Proverbial way of expressing entire freedom from the claiming anything like self-laudation. For sayings of a similar kind among the Fathers, see Suicer, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". I. p. 508. De Wette, following Paulus, thinks that what is referred to is the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "counting",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the money ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "into the left hand",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " before it is given away with the right. This is out of place, for the warning is directed, not against a narrow calculating, but against an ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "ostentatious",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " almsgiving. For the same reason we must object to the view of Luther, who says: “When you are giving alms with the right hand, see that you are not seeking to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "receive",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " more with the left, but rather put it behind your back,” and so on.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
